On 7/12/2010 9:02 AM, Avocado Tom Tarka wrote:

> I know the hose is supposed to be M10 x 1.0, and I also know there's
> a standard size which is very close to the same size.  Based on this
> knowledge and that it won't go in easily, I'm paranoid that the hose
> is wrong and that I'm going to strip the hole (or at least force the
> threads).

I don't know the exact size of the thread (sure someone else will chime 
in), but it is a pipe thread, meaning that the threads taper.  If your 
extension doesn't have a pipe thread, I'd try and find the proper 
connection.  The last thing you want to do is lose oil pressure and kill 
your engine.

Mike
